{"questionId":"17082","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">The solid line in the graph shows the variation with distance <em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math></em> of the displacement <em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math></em> of a travelling wave at <em>t</em> = 0. The dotted line shows the wave 0.20 ms later. The period of the wave is longer than 0.20 ms.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><img style=\"margin-right:auto;margin-left:auto;display:block;\" src=\"__IMG__/d98b300e67319ad5a15523ca0526c72faa03de95.png\" width=\"612\" height=\"296\"></span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Calculate, in Hz, the frequency for this wave.</span></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><em>λ </em>= 0.30 «m» ✔<br><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math> = «<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>250</mn><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>30</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo></math>» 830 «Hz» ✔</span></p>\n<p><em>NOTE: </em><em><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Allow ECF from (a)(i)<br>Allow ECF from wrong wavelength for MP2</span></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"17082","referenceCode":"19N.2.SL.TZ0.3a(ii)","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Calculate, in Hz, the frequency for this wave.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a(ii)","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 4: Waves","4.2 – Travelling waves","Core","Topic 4: Waves"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}